## 1. mbuzz — Best for Validated Attribution

**Why consider mbuzz:** Rockerbox tells you what channels contribute. mbuzz proves it with incrementality testing.

### What mbuzz Offers

**Server-side tracking that captures the full journey.** While Rockerbox uses client-side tracking plus proxy methods for podcasts/TV, mbuzz tracks on your backend—no ad blockers, no missing digital touchpoints. 95%+ event capture vs the 70% typical of client-side tools.

**8 attribution models with side-by-side comparison.** Compare First Touch, Last Touch, Linear, Time Decay, U-Shaped, W-Shaped, plus data-driven Markov Chain and Shapley Value. See how different models credit your channel mix—Rockerbox's MMM gives aggregate insight; mbuzz shows touchpoint-level detail.

**Custom attribution rules for complex funnels.** Define your own logic in minutes:

```ruby
# Multi-channel: Give awareness channels first-touch credit
model "awareness_to_conversion" do
  if position == :first && channel.in?(["podcast", "tv", "influencer"])
    weight 0.40
  elsif position == :last && channel.in?(["paid_search", "retargeting"])
    weight 0.35
  else
    weight :linear
  end
end
```

**LTV attribution that Rockerbox lacks.** Track every recurring payment back to original acquisition source. That podcast sponsor might look expensive on first purchase but deliver 3x LTV—mbuzz shows the full story.

