## The Podcast/TV Attribution Reality

Rockerbox's strength is measuring hard-to-track channels. But be realistic about limitations:

```
Podcast Measurement Reality:
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

What we can track:
├── Vanity URL visits (~10-30% of actual impact)
├── Promo code redemptions (~5-15% of actual impact)
├── Survey responses ("How did you hear about us?")
└── MMM correlation (aggregate, not individual)

What we can't track:
├── Direct website visits from podcast listeners
├── Word of mouth triggered by podcasts
└── Brand recall without immediate action

Reality: All podcast attribution is estimation.
        Rockerbox is best-in-class at estimation,
        but it's still estimation.
```

**Incrementality tests can validate podcast impact** more definitively—turn off podcasts in test markets, measure revenue difference.

